               <head>Letters, Rashiduddin Khan Dihlavi</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Ruqaʿāt by Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān Dihlavī</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85129379 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85076229 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85104368" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4018-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_f7392">Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn Khān Dihlavī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7392">محمّد رشيد الدّين خان دهلوى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7133">Ruqaʿāt</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_7133">رقعات</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Collection of official and private letters by Muḥammad Rashīd al-Dīn, composed in <date calendar="Hijri-qamari">1213</date>, for the benefit of <q>ikhvān al-ṣafāʾ va umarāy va bā vafā va sulṭān-i zamān</q>
                        </p>
                        <p>Comprising a preface and 22 letters, mostly generic, but several with details of historical and social interest. According to William Irvine, the letters are <q>Of no historical value[,] only examples of insha pardazi</q>.
                        </p>
                        <p>Copied at the behest of George Jasper Nicholls from an original lent by <q>Shahzada Mirza Riaz-u-din urf Mirza Shabie (or Shabir) of Benares</q>
                        </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>Copied from an original =-=-=-=-</note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
